snippet.textDisplay:
I have loved MCR since they first came out.
I never had the opportunity to see them in high school as I couldn't afford it. The tickets weren't all that expensive but I was living on my own. So all the money I made at my part time job after school went towards bills and necessities.
Now as an adult, I was so excited that they were going back on tour.
I planned on buying tickets and really wanted to go but was shocked at how expensive they were.
I can't justify spending almost $300 per ticket for my boyfriend and I (So $600 total). Plus travel expenses, food, drink ect.
Honestly, I can't believe they are selling them for such an absurd price and can't help but feel like its a bit of a sell out.
Boo. :(

snippet.textDisplay:
When you're a Christian and like MCR and then watch this video: #awkward Parts of the video made me feel uncomfortable not gonna lie but I'm happy about the representation of the church and the cross. A representation of the good that will triumph in the end in this world. Jesus Christ is coming back for his bride the church one day. He defeated all demons on the cross. He has the victory. Despite what is going on in this world Jesus reigns and that is shown in this video by the cross. I'm choosing to see the good in this video. God can take what the enemy meant for evil and turn it around for good. Many see this video as a representation of evil. I see the part with the church and the cross as a symbol that despite all the evil and darkness in the world hope, light, love, goodness and commitment still prevail. Jesus overcame the evil of this world. No matter how dark it is there is always light, there is always hope. Jesus is the light of the world and when I saw the church and the cross I saw his light shining as a beacon as a lighthouse in an otherwise dark video. Jesus showed up in this video to show people the light, the way out of darkness. Jesus is the light of the world follow him and you will walk in light and not darkness. He loves us with an everlasting love!
He is our living hope because he died but then rose again after 3 days to show that there is life after death for all who believe in him #Jesussaves
